      "content": "Adjusting your inhaler use without professional guidance can be risky, so please do not increase your dosage on your own. Repeatedly needing your inhaler more often is a sign that your asthma might need a review or adjustment to your current treatment plan. For long-term management, consulting your doctor is the safest way to determine if your medication needs tweaking or if further investigation is necessary.",
